    <string name="settings_help_home_relay">Home Relay Server is live in this build for advanced self-hosted setups. Use it only if you already have your own reachable relay, server, NAS, Raspberry Pi, router, or Docker host. Do not expose raw Wake-on-LAN UDP ports directly to the public internet.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_local_wifi">Local Wi-Fi Wake is live in this build. Best first step: tap Auto-detect local network, then enter your PC MAC. This method works only while the phone is on the same Wi-Fi or LAN as the target PC. Ethernet is recommended for the most reliable Wake-on-LAN support, and Wi-Fi wake from shutdown is often hardware-dependent.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_home_device_relay">Home Device Relay is coming later. It is planned for an always-on phone, tablet, Fire TV, Android TV, or Google TV device left at home to receive a secure request and send the local Wake-on-LAN packet.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_smart_plug">Smart Plug Boot Assist is coming later. It is a hardware workaround, not standard Wake-on-LAN. It will require BIOS or UEFI Restore on AC Power Loss support, and power cycling should be used carefully.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_advanced_network">Advanced Network Setup is guides-later content for users who already run router Wake-on-LAN, VPN access, or other custom network paths. It is not a live guided setup in this build.</string>
    <string name="settings_help_smart_home">Smart Home Wake is currently research only. PowerBridge does not yet implement Alexa, Google Home, Home Assistant, or other smart-home wake integrations in this build.</string>
